r size=1> I just wanted to get some thoughts on this.  I'm agnostic, but I tend to lean towards there being nothing after death.  I think it is &quot;lights out&quot;, but I know that there is a chance I could be wrong.  Everyone seems to have a different concept of heaven, and everyone seems to have a different set of rules for getting into heaven.  So, here is my thought:<br>
<br>
Many people feel that if you don't have faith, or if you sin, then you won't get into heaven.  Heaven is described as the ideal place where you will basically feel total exhiliration and be happy for all eternity.  My idea of heaven would be spending an eternity with my husband and son, and anyone who loves their family feels the same way.  Well, let's say I decide tomorrow that I have total faith, and that I live by every single rule in the bible in order to gain passage to heaven.  Now let's say that my husband and son don't follow the same path.  I go up to heaven, but they aren't allowed in.  How can this truly be heaven for me when I have to live through an eternity without the two people I love most?  An eternity without my loved ones would be hell for me.  So, would they get in anyway in order to reward me, or do I get punished regardless of how faithful and good I was?  If I don't get in, then what about my loved ones who went before me that would suffer by watching me get sent below?  Doesn't this seem inconsistent to some people, or is there some other explanation that the various religions have come up with?  I'm just curious.<br>
<br>
Stacey <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#b9a1d0><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub98.ezboard.com/breligiousdebate60574.showUserPublicProfile?gid=bonbon2d>bonbon2D</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Apologist in Training</span><br>  Posts: 59<br> <font color=#3333ff>(1/13/03 3:14 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub98.ezboard.com/freligiousdebate60574frm2.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=66.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.iambornagainru.org/bab/Avatars/cm09.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Heaven: Do We All Go?</span><hr size=1> For me, as an orthodox Christian, I believe that no, not everyone gets to heaven.  <br>
<br>
I've said this before:  It's no fun thinking of loved ones spending eternity in torment...but either I acknowledge it, or I deny Jesus, because He taught frequently of it.  I can't deny Jesus; the evidence for me is too strong that He is who He claimed to be.  So I've got to accept hell.<br>
<br>
God offers Christ, freely and openly.  For me, it's more difficult to understand how a holy and just and good God could allow anyone to go to heaven when everyone deserves hell because all have sinned against Him (Rom. 3:23)<br>
<br>
I don't like the idea that hurricanes sometimes level hundreds of homes and kill scores of people in a single swipe.  But just because I don't like it doesn't deny the reality of it...the same applies to hell.<br>
<br>
THose in heaven are blessed and living in the present, not the past.  I don't see it as possible for those who live in an eternal present to regret and mourn the dead past.<br>
<br>
 <p><!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>Live your life so the preacher won't have to lie at your funeral.</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#9fb7df><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub98.ezboard.com/breligiousdebate60574.showUserPublicProfile?gid=mightyk>MightyK</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Member</span><br>  Posts: 75<br> <font color=#3333ff>(1/13/03 3:26 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub98.ezboard.com/freligiousdebate60574frm2.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=66.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Heaven: Do We All Go?</span><hr size=1> I wouldn't want to go to heaven if my loved ones weren't there. I don't understand this be beyond crap. I'm sorry but that's how it sounds to me. What's so great about heaven if you won't have your loved ones, or even care if you have your loved ones? <br>
<br>
Candy - the one problem I have with your analogy is that God supposidely isn't an unthinking uncaring force of nature. He is suppose to be the Father of us all. What type of father banishes his children from his sight to an eternity of torture and torment? Most people I know of would call a father like that abusive. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :( --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/frown.gif ALT=":("><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
My ideal heaven.... hmmmmm I don't know. Time to study and learn. Gain knowledge, enjoy loved ones, learn to create (paintings, music, poerty, not life). To finally have the damned answers to all those unanswered questions. And lastly, to look at all those fundies who think they were better then everyone else and go &quot;neener neener&quot;. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :hat --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/pimp.gif ALT=":hat"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
Kim <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#b9a1d0><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub98.ezboard.com/breligiousdebate60574.showUserPublicProfile?gid=chakra2@religiousdebate60574>Chakra2</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Member</span><br>  Posts: 5<br> <font color=#3333ff>(1/13/03 4:09 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub98.ezboard.com/freligiousdebate60574frm2.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=66.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Heaven: Do We All Go?</span><hr size=1> I do believe most will be in heaven, besides those that truly are evil.  Even then, I'm not sure if those will remain in a sort of hell as most Christians define it today.<br>
<br>
As already alluded to, I cannot believe that a God who is defined as &quot;love&quot; in His scriptures would damn most of the world to hell.  It makes no sense to me.<br>
<br>
I like to think of heaven as a place where loved ones reunite, and we can further our understanding on spiritual and physical things.  But who's to say what it will be like?  I've often wondered if it will be more a matter of us, energy beings, changing into another form of energy when we die.  I guess in that sense, I also wonder about reincarnation.<br>
<br>
Interesting to ponder...<br>
<br>
Kristin  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#9fb7df><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub98.ezboard.com/breligiousdebate60574.showUserPublicProfile?gid=tinlizzy@religiousdebate60574>TinLizzy</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Member</span><br>  Posts: 16<br> <font color=#3333ff>(1/13/03 4:35 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub98.ezboard.com/freligiousdebate60574frm2.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=66.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Heaven: Do We All Go?</span><hr size=1> I agree with Kristin.  It makes no sense to me to say, &quot;God loves us *so* much that he gives us these complex minds to search and ponder, but if you happen to choose the wrong religion He will banish you to eternal suffering.&quot;  I don't see how anyone who sees God as a loving parent (father) can relate to this--can any of us imagine sentencing our children to spend eternity in hell, no matter what they did?  And my belief is that the love I have for my daughter comes from God, so His love for us must be all the more perfect.<br>
<br>
I also don't think of this belief as denying Jesus.  I have done a lot of research on the topic, and it seems the Bible was written for such specific audiences and has been changed and edited so much to fit certain groups' agendas that what Jesus truly said and meant is not well represented in the Bible we have today.  <br>
<br>
Julie <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#b9a1d0><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub98.ezboard.com/breligiousdebate60574.showUserPublicProfile?gid=kristymom2rainbaby>KristyMom2RaiNBaby</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC="http://babyzone.com/upload/BabyBooks/B/B4B999CD-1-200301101305160656.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Member</span><br>  Posts: 5<br> <font color=#3333ff>(1/13/03 5:03 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub98.ezboard.com/freligiousdebate60574frm2.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=66.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://babyzone.com/upload/BabyBooks/B/B4B999CD-1-200301121435423738.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Heaven: Do We All Go?</span><hr size=1> I am atheist and after we die we are just no longer there....I dunno if I would want to go to heaven if there was such a place anyways...sounds pretty boring!!  I would rather party hardy then be good all the time in Heaven with &quot;god&quot; watchign over me...no on can be good all the time! <p><!--EZCODE CENTER START--><div style="text-align:center"><!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://babyzone.com/upload/BabyBooks/B/B4B999CD-3-200301121455231859.gif"/><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--><!--EZCODE BR START--><br /><!--EZCODE BR END--><!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong><!--EZCODE FONT START--><span style="color:red;">Kristy</span><!--EZCODE FONT END--><!--EZCODE BR START--><br /><!--EZCODE BR END--><!--EZCODE FONT START--><span style="color:silver;">wife to Karl</span><!--EZCODE FONT END--><!--EZCODE BR START--><br /><!--EZCODE BR END--><!--EZCODE FONT START--><span style="color:red;">mommy to Raianna 12/7/00</span><!--EZCODE FONT END--><!--EZCODE BR START--><br /><!--EZCODE BR END--><!--EZCODE FONT START--><span style="color:silver;">and Elyse 12/3/02</span><!--EZCODE FONT END--></strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<!--EZCODE BR START--><br /><!--EZCODE BR END--><!--EZCODE FONT START--><span style="color:red;">A great Greek author N.Kazatzakis once said: <!--EZCODE BR START--><br /><!--EZCODE BR END--><br>
&quot;I believe in nothing I hope for nothing I AM FREE&quot;</span><!--EZCODE FONT END--> <br>
</div><!--EZCODE CENTER END--><br>
</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#9fb7df><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub98.ezboard.com/breligiousdebate60574.showUserPublicProfile?gid=photobug@religiousdebate60574>photobug</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Member</span><br>  Posts: 34<br> <font color=#3333ff>(1/13/03 5:06 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub98.ezboard.com/freligiousdebate60574frm2.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=66.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Heaven: Do We All Go?</span><hr size=1> The short anwer, according to LDS theology, is yes...eventually.  <br>
<br>
We believe that when you die, your spirit leaves your body and goes to the spirit world.  We believe you retain your own personality and tendencies that you have on earth.  We believe that missionary work is going on there too and that many people will hear the Gospel there.  They will have an opportunity to accept it.  However, they will still have to exercise faith because Christ is not living in the spirit world.  The time spent in the spirit world is usually what the bible is talking about when it refers to hell.  It's more of a state of mind than hellfire and brimstone.  And it's not permanent.  When Christ returns to earth in all his glory, the resurrection will begin.  After we are resurrected we will be judged according to our works, knowledge and the desires of our hearts.  We will then be placed in a degree of glory.  The Celestial Kingdom is where God dwells.  Christ rules the Terrestrial Kingdom and the Telestial kingdom has the influence of the Holy Ghost.  All 3 are part of &quot;heaven&quot; and where we will spend eternity.  We will continue to learn and grow and we will be with our families.  We're also taught that everyone will be happy/comfortable with where they end up.  <br>
<br>
There is a 4th place where Satan and his followers will spend eternity.  This is outer darkness.  It is reserved for Satan and the spirits that followed him and never received a body.  Also for the sons of perdition.  These are people who had a sure knowledge of Christ and then denied his existence.  The Bible referrs to it as blaspheming the Holy Spirit.  <br>
<br>
-Misty <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#b9a1d0><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub98.ezboard.com/breligiousdebate60574.showUserPublicProfile?gid=gaia25>Gaia25</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Member</span><br>  Posts: 80<br> <font color=#3333ff>(1/13/03 6:35 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub98.ezboard.com/freligiousdebate60574frm2.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=66.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Heaven: Do We All Go?</span><hr size=1> I've always been puzzled by the &quot;who gets to go&quot; thing.  It would only be heaven for me if my mum and dad, grandparents, aunts, uncles, cousins, brother, sisters, husband and kids were all there too (along with assorted friends, pets, and chocolate! <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :lol --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/laugh.gif ALT=":lol"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> )...I don't understand the &quot;eternal present&quot; thing..so you don't miss everyone who ever meant anything to you.<br>
<br>
What is the point in eternity if you don't get to spend it with people you love? <p><!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://www.growthspurts.com/drivee/images/434360233606.jpg"/><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#9fb7df><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub98.ezboard.com/breligiousdebate60574.showUserPublicProfile?gid=powertotherae>Powertotherae</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Member</span><br>  Posts: 32<br> <font color=#3333ff>(1/13/03 6:55 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub98.ezboard.com/freligiousdebate60574frm2.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=66.topic&index=8>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Heaven: Do We All Go?</span><hr size=1> I have no clue and honestly don't care. Since I am an Atheist and don't believe in god they I couldn't really believe that there is a heaven. I think Heaven and Hell are right here on earth. I think the concept of heaven is one made up to control the masses. I think it is really sad that people spend there whole lives worry about what will happen to them when they are dead. What is the purpose? It is like you never really lived.<br>
